The special thing about the personal online data storage is that the user can decide who can access which data alone.
The company describes this concept as personal reinforcement and data development.
According to CEO John Bruce, the idea behind Inrupt is that the Company uses resources, processes, and capabilities to make Solid available to all.
The company currently includes Berners-Lee, Bruce, some developers who have been hired to work on this project, as well as a community of volunteer programmers. Furthermore, a security platform acquired by IBM is used.
At the beginning of this week, technology developers will be able to create their own decentralized apps worldwide using the tools available on the Inrupt website.
Berners-Lee announced that he and his team will not discuss with Facebook and Google whether a comprehensive change should be made, in which their entire business models will be completely redesigned overnight.
"We do not ask for their permission."
In an article on Medium published on Saturday, Berners-Lee wrote that Inrupt has the task of providing commercial energy generation and an ecosystem to protect the integrity and quality of the new, solid-based web.
In 1994, Berners-Lee created the World Wide Web Consortium at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology.
In recent months, Berners-Lee has been instrumental in the debate on net neutrality.
Even with the launch of Inrupt, Berners-Lee remains the founder and director of the World Wide Web Consortium, the Web Foundation and the Open Data Institute.
"I am extremely confident about this new era of the web," he added.
