Later, he advanced to the fire line and led the line forward with the "greatest bravery" before rushing alone with a field weapon and shutting down three of the military units.
Lieutenant Colonel Vann was shot by a German sniper on 4 October 1918; just over a month before the end of the war.
Michael Vann, 72, said that his grandfather's actions were something he could never do justice to, and at the same time something that makes you humble.
Together with his brother Dr. James Vann, he laid down a wreath after the parade under the direction of the Brentwood Imperial Youth Band.
