This was the first time that the Navy returned a ship to the shipyard after its delivery.
Little was known about the reasons for the return, but German media mentioned a number of important "software and hardware errors" that would have made the new ship unusable in a battle situation.
Software problems are particularly serious, as ships of the Baden-Württemberg-Class are operated by a crew of only 120 sailors, only about half as many as on the older frigates of the Bremen-Class.
